## Enable or disable autopay

> Sample Request

```json
{
  "unbillKey": "<%= config.auth %>",
  "userId": "566595c8ce88ccec69328566",
  "companyId": "56e1dbb5443b10a3bd403fcf",
  "autopay": "disabled"
}
```

> 400 Response

```json
{
  "message": "We couldn't disable auto pay for this company, sorry."
}
```

Enable or disable autopay for a bill.

Some subscription billers, such as Netflix, Hulu, and Spotify require automatic payments to be enabled. If a request to the `/payment/autopay` endpoint is made for one of these billers, a `400` status code will be returned and autopay will not be disabled.

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config.host %>/payment/autopay`

### Post Parameters

Param | Description
----- | -----------
`userId` | Unbill user ID.
`companyId` | Unbill company ID.
`autopay` | Whether autopay should be enabled or disabled. `enabled, disabled`

### Returns

Returns a `200` status code if autopay was enabled or disabled.